FILE LIST:
==========
HTML Files:
- login.htm - User login page for existing customers
- register.htm - User registration page for new customers
- listing.htm - Item listing page for sellers to add auction items
- bidding.htm - Auction bidding page to view and bid on items
- maintenance.htm - System maintenance page for processing auctions and reports

PHP Files:
- login.php - Handle user authentication against customer XML database
- register.php - Handle new customer registration and email confirmation
- listing.php - Handle item listing and add to auction XML database
- placeBid.php - Handle bid placement with validation
- buyNow.php - Handle buy-it-now purchases
- processAuctions.php - Process expired auctions and update statuses
- generateReport.php - Generate sales report and remove sold/failed items
- logout.php - Handle user logout and session cleanup
- getAuctions.php - Get auction data in XML format for AJAX requests

JavaScript Files:
- common.js - Common AJAX functions, form handlers, and utilities

Style Files:
- style/style.css - CSS styling for consistent application appearance

XSLT Files:
- report.xsl - XSLT stylesheet for report generation and formatting

Data Files (in www/data/ directory):
- customer.xml - Customer database with user credentials
- auction.xml - Auction items database with current listings
- report.xml - Generated reports for sold/failed items

SYSTEM INSTRUCTIONS:
====================
1. Start from login.htm or register.htm for new users
2. Login with existing credentials or register new account
3. Use Listing page to add items for auction with required details
4. Use Bidding page to view all auction items and place bids
5. Use Maintenance page to process expired auctions and generate reports
6. System automatically refreshes auction data every 5 seconds on bidding page
7. Log out when finished using the system

